Program

Opportunity

The conference provides opportunities for the FOSS4G community to learn, explore, share, and collaborate on the latest ideas and information.

FOSS4G NA is all about community. Contributors, adopters, users, extenders, teachers, service providers, consumers and business and research organizations gather to share their expertise and learn from each other. FOSS4G delivers camaraderie and networking opportunities that lead to synergies in the community, as well as opportunities to give and receive help on specific technical issues or to generate business opportunities.

Program 2019

The program is also available on your mobile device for offline use and planning your schedule. Download the Attendify mobile app from the Google Play or Apple App Store, search events for “FOSS4G NA 2019”, and add the event to browse the program at your convenience.

The program is still provisional and subject to change. Email us at program@foss4g-na.org with any special requests.

 

Sun April 14

Code Sprint at UCSD, Geisel Library, Redwood Conference Room from 10am to 6pm. No-host Happy Hour at Rock Bottom Restaurant and Brewery (La Jolla) from 6pm to 8pm. After hours at SD TapRoom (Garnet Ave., Pacific Beach).

More information on OSGeo Wiki
